; Stage 13 L1 — cfn escape analysis (negative fixture).
;
; A cfn captures each used local BY REFERENCE: its environment is a struct of
; pointers into the captured storage, so the closure value INHERITS the region of
; each captured referent. Returning it out of the referent's scope would dangle,
; so the frame-region escape analysis rejects the return.
;
; This fixture is intentionally not a runnable program (no main). Compiling it
; must FAIL with the escape error:
;   "address of frame-local storage escapes via return — the pointed-to storage
;    is reclaimed when this function returns"
; which proves the cfn inherits its captured local's region and the return sink
; catches the escape.

(import-use allocator)

; `x` is a plain frame local (a let binding). The cfn captures it by reference,
; so the closure value is tainted with x's frame region. Returning the closure
; escapes that region and is rejected.
(defn escapes:i32 ()
  (let (x:i32 5)
    (let (h:ref:AllocHandle (default-allocator))
      (return (cfn h ():i32 (return x))))))
